aragon-ai (1.3.5) stable; urgency=low

  * Move cache dir from /root/.cache/llama.cpp/ to /var/cache/llama.cpp/
    Background: /root/.cache/llama.cpp/ exists on lowerdir (mmcblk2p8) — born 2024-08-21, it was baked into the factory image. 
    When llama.cpp creates a new file there, overlay must copy-up the existing directory from mmcblk2p8 to the upperdir 
    on mmcblk2p9 while mmcblk2p8 is also the source of the lowerdir. Both partitions are on the same eMMC chip. The 
    simultaneous read (copy-up source) + mmap write (copy-up destination) + token generation (CPU at full load) on a 
    single eMMC with rootflags=discard active causes the eMMC controller to hit a 
    command queue conflict — hard reset, no kernel panic.

 -- root <jens@proknx.com>  Tue, 01 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0100

